title: Overview of the SPIAT package
text: SPIAT (Spatial Image Analysis Tissues) R package suite data processing, quality control, visualization, data handling data analysis tools (Yang et al. 2020). SPIAT directly compatible Opal multiplex immunohistochemistry images analysed HALO InForm analysis software, intuitive implementation allows use diversity platforms. Opal multiplex immunohistochemistry staining protocol enables 6-8 tissue markers used simultaneously single slide. suitable use formalin fixed paraffin embedded (FFPE) tissue sections, also relevance clinical practice. fluorescence marker measured imaging, cell assigned X,Y coordinate location. effect provides single-cell resolution. fluorescence intensity individual markers combined identify phenotype cells tissue. SPIAT includes novel algorithms identification cell clusters, cell margins cell gradients, calculation neighbourhood proportions, algorithms prediction cell phenotypes tissue images. SPIAT also includes speedy implementations calculation cell distances detection cell communities. overview functions available shown figure .

title: Overview of the SPIAT package
text: First load SPIAT library. can use format_image_to_sce read format raw data SPIAT.format_image_to_sce creates SingleCellExperiment object. requires least 4 arguments: format: “INFORM,” “HALO,” “Visium,” “CODEX” “cellprolifer, ”general" image: path raw InForm HALO image data file markers: names markers used OPAL staining. must order marker columns input file, InForm must match marker name used input file. One markers must DAPI. locations: locations markers, either Nucleus, Cytoplasm Membrane. must order markers. locations used auto-detect intensity (dye) columns. Alternatively, column names can specified, see information.
code: library(SPIAT)

title: Overview of the SPIAT package
text: SPIAT can predict cell phenotypes using marker intensity levels predict_phenotypes. can used check phenotypes assigned InForm HALO. can also potentially used automate manual phenotypying performed InForm/HALO. predict_phenotypes produces density plot shows cutoff calling cell positive marker. also prints console number true positives (TP), true negatives (TN), false positives (FP) false negatives (FN). returns table containing phenotypes predicted SPIAT actual phenotypes InForm/HALO. can help show need go back Inform HALO refine phenotyping. don’t tumour_marker can use marker present many cells, least one peak main marker peak, background peak, required algorithm. note, algorithm take account cell shape size, required phenotyping, manual phenotyping HALO InForm recommended.      can use marker_prediction_plot plot predicted cell phenotypes ones obtained using HALO InForm, comparison.  plot shows Immune_marker1+ cells tissue. left Immune_marker1+ cells defined InForm right Immune_marker1+ cells predicted using SPIAT. Similar plots generated markers. example, following plots Tumour_marker. Use predicted phenotypes replace original ones.      Define predicted image apply tSNE dimensionality reduction plot predicted image.

title: Overview of the SPIAT package
text: Cross K function similar mixing score, calculates score across possible distances. also compares behaviour image image randomly distributed points number. 4 patterns can distinguished K-cross function, illustrated plots (generated ).  , black line represents image, red line represents randomly distibuted point pattern. 1st plot: red line black line close , means two types points randomly independently distributed. 2nd plot: red line black line, middle difference dramatic, means points mixed split clusters. 3rd plot: increase radius, black line diverges red line, means one mixed cluster two types points. 4th plot: red line black line, means two types points form separated clusters. can calculate cross K-function using SPIAT. another pattern cross K curve identified previously, “ring” one cell type surrounding area another cell type. pattern, observed expected curves cross K function crossing. observed crossing many example images rings exist. However, crossing exclusively present ring images. separate clusters two cell types close, crossing can also happen low distance. images infiltration, crossing may also happen extremely low distance due randomness. use crossing metric indicating ring pattern, need choose reasonable distance cross K function (generally quarter half image size, also consider cluster size), filter extremely low crossing distance. result shows crossing happens 50% specified distance (100) cross K function, close edge tumour cluster. means crossing due randomness cell distribution, due two close located immune tumour clusters. result aligns observation immune ring surrounding tumour cluster. can calculate area curve (AUC) cross K-function. tells us two types cells : separate clusters - negative independent/immune ring - closer zero mixed - positive AUC score close zero tells us two types cells either relationship form ring surrounding cluster.

title: Overview of the SPIAT package
text: image image_no_markers simulated package spaSim. image contains “Tumour,” “Immune,” “Immune1” “Immune2” cells without marker intensities.  can determine aggregates (lack aggregates) particular phenotype combination cell types. SPIAT can used identify two types cell aggregates, clusters communities. Clusters cell aggregates composed non-tumour cells, often immune cells. detection clusters, identify_cell_clusters considers cell types interest defined user. Euclidean distances cells calculated, pairs cells distance less threshold considered ‘interacting,’ rest ‘non-interacting.’ Hierarchical clustering used separate clusters. need specify radius. radius corresponds lenient defining clusters. bigger radius mean likely merge individual clusters. radius chosen based looks ‘reasonable.’ Cells assigned clusters (“free” cells) assigned Cluster_NA output table. argument min_neighborhood_size specifies threshold neighborhood size considered neighborhood. clustering methods include dbscan Rphenograph.  plot shows clusters Immune, Immune1 Immune2 cells. number colour corresponds distinct cluster. Black cells correspond ‘free,’ un-clustered cells. Users recommended test different radius visualize clustering results. SPIAT also average_minimum_distance, calculates average minimum distance cells image, can used starting point. can visualize cell composition neighborhoods. allows us determine whether regions cells different types interacting, whether little mixing celltypes. , can use composition_of_neighborhoods obtain percentages cells specific marker within neighborhood number cells neighborhood. can use plot_composition_heatmap produce heatmap showing marker percentages within cluster.  plot shows Cluster_1 CLuster_2 contain three types immune cells. Cluster_3 Immune1. Cluster_1 Cluster_2 similar free cells composition.
code: data("image_no_markers")  plot_cell_categories(image_no_markers, c("Tumour", "Immune","Immune1","Immune2","Others"),                      c("red","blue","darkgreen", "brown","lightgray"),"Cell.Type") clusters <- identify_neighborhoods(image_no_markers,                                     method = "hierarchical",                                    min_neighborhood_size = 100,                                    cell_types_of_interest = c("Immune", "Immune1", "Immune2"),                                     radius = 50, feature_colname = "Cell.Type") average_minimum_distance(formatted_image) ## [1] 17.01336 neighorhoods_vis <- composition_of_neighborhoods(clusters, feature_colname = "Cell.Type") neighorhoods_vis <- neighorhoods_vis[neighorhoods_vis$Total_number_of_cells >=5,] plot_composition_heatmap(neighorhoods_vis, feature_colname="Cell.Type")

title: format_image_to_sce — format_image_to_sce
text: format String defining software used cell segmentation. Options: "INFORM", "HALO", "Visium", "CODEX" "cellprolifer, "general" path String path location either HALO csv file, INFORM text file CODEX csv file. 10X Visium transcriptomics data, path "filtered_feature_bc_matrix" folder generated CellRanger. markers INFORM HALO formats. Vector containing markers used staining. Must match order 'markers' parameter locations Vector containing locations markers used staining. Location can either "Nucleus", "Cytoplasm" "Membrane". used select Intensity column can used instead intensity_columns_interest. dye_columns_interest HALO formats. Use locations specified. Vector names columns marker status (.e. indicating 1 0 whether cell positive negative marker). Column names must match order 'markers' parameter. intensity_columns_interest HALO formats. Use locations specified. Vector names columns level marker. Column names must match order 'markers' parameter. path_to_visium_coordinates 10X Visium data. String path "tissue_positions_list.csv" generated CellRanger. path_to_codex_cell_phenotypes CODEX data. String path Cluster ID/Cell type file. intensity_matrix "general" format. matrix marker intensities gene expression column names Cell IDs, rownames marker genes. phenotypes vector cell phenotypes order appear intensity_matrix. phenotypes available, vector NA can used input. Note combination markers (e.g. CD3,CD4) needs used instead cell type name (e.g. helper T cells) coord_x vector X coordinates cells. cells must order intensity_matrix. coord_y vector Y coordinates cells. cells must order intensity_matrix.
